title: (x) Cherry Creek Mortgage Company logo - Janson Text {Eric Schmid}
content:
I have looked through all my fonts but this one eludes me. It must be a common one.

 ![](http://web.archive.org/files/cherrycrk_4586.jpg)
author: vector

comments.content: It’s eluding you because it’s been [squooshed](http://web.archive.org/wiki/squooshed).
In the Midwest we call it squarshed

Found it - Janson Text Bold

squarshed and stretched, I’m sure just like the font designer intended it to look :/
squarshed is much better than sqooshed!
